{{Infobox organization | name = Kalamazoo Book Arts Center | logo = File:Kalamazoo Book Arts Center logo.jpg | formation = {{Start date|2005}} | founder = | founding_location = | extinction = <!-- use {{end date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | merger = | type = | tax_id = <!-- or | vat_id = (for European organizations) --> | registration_id = <!-- for non-profit org --> | status = | purpose = Exploring the art of handmade paper, prints, books and the ideas within them | headquarters = | location = Kalamazoo, Michigan | coords = <!-- {{coord|LAT|LON|display=inline, title}} --> | region = | services = | products = | methods = | fields = | membership = | membership_year = | language = | owner = <!-- or | owners = --> | sec_gen = | leader_title = | leader_name = | board_of_directors = | slogan = | website = {{URL|kalbookarts.org/}} | remarks = | formerly = | footnotes = }}
The '''Kalamazoo Book Arts Center (KBAC)''' is a nonprofit organization of artists and writers located in [[Kalamazoo, Michigan]].
== History == KBAC was founded by Jeff Abshear<ref name="Gilmore"/> in 2005 to create a community workshop and educational space focused on the arts of [[book design]] and [[printing]], fine [[printmaking]], [[papermaking]], [[bookbinding]], and [[creative writing]].<ref name="ArtsCouncil">{{cite web|title=Kalamazoo Book Arts Center|url=http://www.kalamazooarts.org/organization/kalamazoo-book-arts-center/|website=Arts Council of Greater Kalamazoo|accessdate=9 April 2018}}</ref> The center is located at the Park Trades Center on Kalamazoo Avenue in downtown Kalamazoo.<ref name="PlazaCorp">{{cite web|title=Park Trades Center|url=http://plazacorp.net/commercial/park-trades-center/|website=PlazaCorp|accessdate=9 April 2018}}</ref> The organization is supported by grants (including the [[National Endowment for the Arts]]), and community support.<ref name="kbac">{{cite web|title=Mission|url=http://kalbookarts.org/mission/|website=Kalamazoo Book Arts Center|accessdate=9 April 2018}}</ref>
== Programs == KBAC has regular on-site book arts workshops.<ref name="Workshops">{{cite web|title=Workshops|url=http://kalbookarts.org/workshops/|website=Kalamazoo Book Arts Center|accessdate=9 April 2018}}</ref> KBAC created and hosts the "Poets in Print" reading series.<ref name="Milkweed">{{cite web|title=Kathy Fagan and Christopher Kempf at Kalamazoo Book Arts Center|url=https://milkweed.org/event/kathy-fagan-and-christopher-kempf-at-kalamazoo-book-arts-center|website=Milkweed Editions|accessdate=26 May 2018}}</ref><ref name="Gilmore">{{cite web|title=Kalamazoo Book Arts Center|url=http://www.isgilmore.org/2014/01/20/kalamazoo-book-arts-center/|website=Irving S. Gilmore Foundation|accessdate=26 May 2018}}</ref> KBAC participates in the ''Arts Council of Greater Kalamazoo's'' monthly ''Art Hop!''<ref name="acgk">{{cite web|title=Organizations|url=http://www.kalamazooarts.org/organization/?page=2|website=Arts Council of Greater Kalamazoo|accessdate=26 May 2018}}</ref>
