{{For|other people named Robert Gifford|Robert Gifford (disambiguation){{!}}Robert Gifford}} {{Infobox scientist | name = Robert Gifford | image = Robert Gifford PhD.jpg | image_size = 150 px | alt = | caption = | birth_date = | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | residence = Victoria, BC | citizenship = | nationality = | fields = [[environmental psychology]], [[social psychology]], [[personality psychology]] | workplaces = [[University of Victoria]] | alma_mater = [[Simon Fraser University]], [[University of California, Davis]] | doctoral_advisor = | academic_advisors = [[Robert Sommer]] | doctoral_students = | notable_students = | known_for = | influences = | influenced = | awards = | signature = <!-- (filename only) --> | signature_alt = | footnotes = }} '''Robert Gifford''' is professor of [[Psychology]] and Environmental Studies at the [[University of Victoria]] ([[British Columbia]], Canada). His main research interests are [[environmental psychology]], [[social psychology]], and [[personality psychology]]. He has worked on nonverbal behavior<ref name=NYT>{{cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1991/09/17/science/non-verbal-cues-are-easy-to-misinterpret.html |title=Non-Verbal Cues Are Easy to Misinterpret - NYTimes.com |first=Daniel|last=Goleman |work=[[The New York Times|New York Times]] |date=1991-09-17 |accessdate=2010-08-04 }}</ref> and on climate change behavior barriers.<ref name=pmid19847247>{{cite journal |author=Gifford R |title=Q&A: The science of persuasion. Interview by Sanjay Khanna |journal=[[Nature (journal)|Nature]] |volume=461 |issue=7267 |pages=1059 |date=October 2009 |pmid=19847247 |doi=10.1038/4611059a |url=http://www.nature.com/nature/journal/v461/n7267/full/4611059a.html |accessdate=2010-08-04 }}</ref><ref name=PRI>{{cite web |url = http://www.pri.org/science/environment/psychology-climate-inaction1538.html |title = The psychology of climate inaction |work = Public Radio International |date = 2009-08-09 |accessdate = 2010-08-04 |archiveurl = https://www.webcitation.org/5xjgkEKeD?url=http://www.pri.org/science/environment/psychology-climate-inaction1538.html |archivedate = 2011-04-06 |deadurl = yes |df = }}</ref> Gifford is the author of 5 editions of ''Environmental Psychology: Principles and Practice'', which has also been translated into Japanese, and edited ''Research Methods for Environmental Psychology'' (2016). From 2004 to 2016, he was the [[editor in chief]] of the ''[[Journal of Environmental Psychology]].''<ref name=JEP>{{cite web |url=http://www.elsevier.com/wps/find/journaleditorialboard.cws_home/622872/editorialboard |title=Journal of Environmental Psychology - Editorial Board |format= |work=Elsevier |accessdate=2010-08-04 }}</ref> Gifford also serves on the [[editorial board]]s of ''[[Architectural Science Review]]''<ref name=ASRE>{{cite web |url=http://www.earthscan.co.uk/Default.aspx?tabid=101732 |title=Architectural Science Review - Editorial Board |format= |work=Earthscan |accessdate=2010-08-04 }}</ref> and ''[[Applied Psychology (journal)|Applied Psychology]]''.<ref name=AP>{{cite web |url=http://www.wiley.com/bw/editors.asp?ref=0269-994X&site=1 |title=Applied Psychology: An International Review - Journal Information |format= |work=[[Wiley-Blackwell]] |accessdate=2010-08-04 }}</ref> In addition, he has served as President of the environmental divisions of the [[American Psychological Association]], the [[International Association of Applied Psychology]], and the [[Canadian Psychological Association]].
